Create a high-performance 3D multiplayer aerial arena game titled Neon Drift Dominion using Three.js and Firebase.

1. Branding and UI:
- Display a sleek holographic header with the brand name in bright electric violet and aqua.
- Include an Open in New Tab button and a Store button for premium purchases.
- Use a futuristic HUD with score, boost meter, shield level, and capture progress.
- Ensure all HTML UI overlays never block pointer events on the 3D canvas except for explicit buttons.

2. Core Game Design:
- Replace traditional airplane models with stylized anti-gravity gliders shaped like winged drone-craft, featuring curved neon fins and rotating energy stabilizers.
- Use a 3rd-person floating chase camera with subtle camera tilt, motion smoothing, and speed-based zoom.
- Movement should feel arcade-smooth rather than realistic simulation: accelerate, brake, strafe-drift, vertical lift, and short blink-dash.
- Controls:
  - WASD / Arrow Keys = movement
  - Shift = boost
  - Q / E = side drift
  - Space = deploy pulse wave
  - Left Click = energy tether
- Instead of standard shooting combat, players compete to capture floating Energy Rings scattered across the arena.
- Players can tether to Energy Rings, charge them for their team, and steal partially charged rings from opponents.
- Add temporary power-ups such as shield burst, overdrive speed, EMP pulse, and score multiplier.

3. Multiplayer (Firebase):
- Use Firebase Realtime Database for live synchronization of player transform, velocity state, active power-up, team color, and score.
- Support drop-in/drop-out multiplayer sessions with automatic cleanup of inactive players.
- Include a live global leaderboard and also a session-based team scoreboard.
- Add team matchmaking logic for two teams: Violet and Cyan.
- Sync ring capture progress in real time so all players see contested objectives instantly.

4. Monetization (PayPal):
- Integrate the PayPal JavaScript SDK with clear placeholder configuration.
- Build a purchase flow for premium glider skins, trail effects, and season pass access.
- On successful payment approval, unlock the purchased cosmetic in Firebase and trigger a celebratory particle burst around the player.
- Include boilerplate placeholders for secure server-side order creation and capture verification.

5. Visual Direction:
- Set the arena above a glowing cloud city at dusk with layered skyboxes, volumetric fog, and animated light highways below.
- Apply a neon-futuristic arcade style with emissive materials, bloom, speed trails, animated capture rings, and reflective metallic surfaces.
- Include optimized particle effects, low-latency animation updates, and performance-conscious rendering suitable for browser play.

6. Technical Requirements:
- Use modular, production-friendly code structure.
- Include complete boilerplate with:
  - Three.js scene setup
  - player controller
  - arena and capture ring system
  - Firebase config placeholders
  - PayPal config placeholders
  - leaderboard UI
  - store UI
- Add comments indicating where to insert API keys, Firebase credentials, and PayPal client credentials.


Create a production-ready 3D multiplayer browser game titled Neon Drift Dominion using Three.js, Firebase Realtime Database, and PayPal Checkout.

Requirements:
- Use futuristic anti-gravity gliders instead of traditional airplanes.
- Focus gameplay on team-based capture objectives rather than simple shooting.
- Implement a secure monetization flow where PayPal payment approval does not directly grant rewards on the client.
- Require server-side order creation, capture verification, and then update the player's Firebase inventory only after successful verification.
- Include placeholders for sandbox and live PayPal environments.
- Prepare the project for global web deployment with English UI, responsive layout, and scalable architecture.
- Make the project easy to deploy as a web game.
